    "what_description": "Eurycoma longifolia is a tropical tree native to Southeast Asia, belonging to the family Simaroubaceae. It is characterized by its long, pointed leaves that are dark green in color and have a leathery texture, typically growing in clusters at the ends of branches. The tree can grow up to 10 meters in height, with a straight trunk and a broad, rounded crown. Eurycoma longifolia is commonly known as the \"Tongkat Ali\" tree, and its roots have been used in traditional medicine for their potential adaptogenic and tonic properties. The tree's roots contain a high concentration of the bioactive compound eurycomanone, which is responsible for its medicinal properties.",
