    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Eurycoma longifolia are attributed to its ability to exhibit antioxidant properties, which help protect cells from oxidative damage and prevent chronic diseases. The anti-inflammatory properties of Eurycoma longifolia have been shown to reduce inflammation and alleviate symptoms associated with various conditions, including arthritis. Additionally, its antimicrobial properties make it effective in combating infections caused by bacteria, fungi, and viruses. The antioxidant neuroprotective properties of Eurycoma longifolia have been found to have neuroprotective effects, suggesting its potential in the prevention and treatment of neurodegenerative diseases. Furthermore, its immunomodulatory properties enable it to regulate the immune system, which can help in the management of autoimmune diseases and conditions with compromised immune function.",
