    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Eurycoma longifolia are eurycomanone, eurycolactone, eurycomanol, eurycomanin, and quercetin. Eurycomanone has been shown to possess anti-cancer properties by inhibiting the growth of cancer cells and inducing apoptosis, while also exhibiting anti-inflammatory and antioxidant activities. Eurycolactone has been found to have anti-angiogenic properties, suppressing the formation of new blood vessels that feed cancer cells. Eurycomanol has been reported to have immunomodulatory effects, enhancing immune function and protecting against oxidative stress, while eurycomanin has been shown to exhibit anti-inflammatory and antioxidant activities. Quercetin, a flavonoid present in Eurycoma longifolia, has been demonstrated to possess anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, and anti-cancer properties, as well as modulating the immune response to prevent disease progression.",
