    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Eurycoma longifolia are tincture, capsules, tea, eurycoma extract, and oil. Tincture is a concentrated liquid solution typically made with the plant's roots or seeds in a solvent like ethanol or glycerin, providing a bioavailable form of the herb. Capsules contain a standardized extract of the plant, often providing a precise dosage of the key compounds, such as eurycomanone and eurycomalactone. Eurycoma tea is prepared by infusing the plant's roots or seeds in hot water, releasing its bioactive compounds, although the efficacy may be lower compared to other preparations. Eurycoma extract and oil are highly concentrated forms of the herb, often obtained through solvent extraction or distillation, and are commonly used in supplements and topical applications.",
