    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Eurycoma longifolia improperly include experiencing nausea due to its high content of bioactive compounds, which can cause gastrointestinal disturbances. This is because Eurycoma longifolia contains flavonoids and alkaloids that can stimulate the digestive system and lead to nausea. Additionally, developing a headache is also a possible side effect as the plant's bioactive compounds can cause vasodilation, leading to increased blood flow to the brain and potentially resulting in headaches. Furthermore, using Eurycoma longifolia improperly can lead to kidney damage due to its high levels of flavonoids, which can be nephrotoxic in large quantities. Suffers kidney damage can also occur if the plant's bioactive compounds accumulate in the body and cause oxidative stress, potentially leading to hypertension and other cardiovascular issues."
